#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
freshness-audit — Script 2 of 5 for the ClarityRev 25-niche evaluation pipeline.

Audits a completed niche canvas for source data freshness before finalization.
Implements:
  1. Source-count-based staleness ratio (§6.4)
  2. Claim-weighted staleness ratio — the Eye Security bug fix (§6.4)
     A single stale source supplying >20% of claims blocks the canvas
     regardless of source-count ratio.
  3. BLOCK-class hard enforcement for JOB/HIRING/INTENT data types (§6.1)
  4. Retroactive content-hash comparison for HIGHEST-priority data types (§6.5)

Usage:
    ./freshness-audit NICHE_ID [--force] [--dry-run]

Exit codes:
    0  PASS       — All sources fresh, canvas ready for finalization
    1  BLOCKED    — Blocking staleness found
    2  WARNING    — Non-blocking staleness (0% < stale_ratio <= 10%)
    3  INTERNAL_ERROR — Script bug, missing dependency, corrupted YAML
    4  INVALID_INPUT  — NICHE_ID malformed or trace-map not found

Design principles (Google SRE):
  - Idempotent: running twice with same inputs produces same result
  - Explicit error boundaries: every file read / YAML parse has defined failure mode
  - Observable outputs: structured JSON to stdout, human-readable logs to stderr
  - Graceful degradation: non-critical failures produce degraded results, not crashes
"""

